The course will cover general terms of the field, give an overview of the purposes and ground documents of describing, classification and subject indexing different kinds of information, introduce the techniques of describing, classification and subject indexing, give an overview of metadata standards and principles of use of metadata.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to give to the students theoretical knowledge and basic practical skills on describing,  classification and subject indexing of different kinds of information resource and information carriers .Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who has passed the course will: - know the metadata standards; - have theoretical knowledge of describing, classification and subject indexing; - know the purposes of and requirements set on describing, classification and subject indexing; - have an overview of the specific guidelines, rules and standards; - use correctly the basic terms and have an overview about the main topics of subject; - acquire basic skills on describing, classification and subject indexing various kinds of information resource and information carriers .
